	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97439186729091><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97439186729091>RE: Learning Bonds of Force usage</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97439186729091#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 16th 11:24 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>What I have found best is if your bonds of force wears off use your tishan's clash to stun them, then recast bonds of force, much better than rooting I think.&nbsp;&nbsp;This gives you the ability to recast BoF without having them charge you and casting your snare on your self by accident.  If you go to attempt this becareful because you must react very fast (stun only lasts for maybe 2 or 3 seconds), so it takes a little practice but once you get it down helps a lot.<br><br>Gondolf Goblinslayer,<br>30th Wizard, Tallon Zek<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
